<subSubSection pageId="17" pageNumber="544" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="17.[151,1437,259,789]" pageId="17" pageNumber="544">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,322,331,357]" pageId="17" pageNumber="544">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
This new species is similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="He, Chen &amp; van Achterberg" authorityName="He, Chen &amp; van Achterberg" authorityYear="1997" box="[658,1141,331,358]" class="Insecta" family="Braconidae" genus="Chelonus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="544" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sinensis" subGenus="Scabrichelonus">
<emphasis box="[658,684,332,358]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="544">C.</emphasis>
(
<emphasis box="[699,720,331,357]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="544">S.</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis box="[735,824,332,357]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="544">sinensis</emphasis>
He, Chen &amp; van Achterberg
</taxonomicName>
, but can be separated from the latter by the following characters: hind coxa and hind femur black in both sexes (hind coxa apically and hind femur basally more or less yellowish-brown in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="He, Chen &amp; van Achterberg" authorityYear="1997" box="[681,850,403,430]" class="Insecta" family="Braconidae" genus="Chelonus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="544" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sinensis" subGenus="Scabrichelonus">
<emphasis box="[681,707,404,430]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="544">C.</emphasis>
(
<emphasis box="[724,745,403,429]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="544">S.</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis box="[761,850,404,429]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="544">sinensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
); apical opening of male carapace is relatively large and close to lateral margins of carapace (apical opening of male carapace relatively small and remaining removed from lateral margins of carapace).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="19" lastPageNumber="546" pageId="17" pageNumber="544" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="17.[151,1437,259,789]" box="[199,1068,511,538]" pageId="17" pageNumber="544">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,345,511,537]" pageId="17" pageNumber="544">Description.</emphasis>
<typeStatus box="[352,459,511,537]" pageId="17" pageNumber="544">Holotype</typeStatus>
, female, length of body 
<quantity box="[730,818,511,538]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.5" pageId="17" pageNumber="544" unit="mm" value="4.5">4.5 mm</quantity>
, of fore wing 
<quantity box="[975,1064,511,538]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.4" pageId="17" pageNumber="544" unit="mm" value="3.4">3.4 mm</quantity>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="17.[151,1437,259,789]" pageId="17" pageNumber="544">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,270,547,573]" pageId="17" pageNumber="544">Head.</emphasis>
Antennomeres more than 8 (broken in 
<typeStatus box="[701,803,547,573]" pageId="17" pageNumber="544">holotype</typeStatus>
), scapus robust, length of third antennomere 1.2 × fourth, length of third and fourth antennomeres 3.8 × and 3.3 × their width, respectively; in dorsal view its maximum width and width between eyes 1.2 × and 1.8 × its median length, respectively; temple strongly swollen posteriorly; frons slightly concave; temple and vertex distinctly transversely rugose; OOL: OD: POL= 21: 9: 11; longitudinal diameter of eye 0.8 × height of temples (
<figureCitation box="[558,663,691,717]" captionStart="FIGURE 14" captionStartId="16.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[179,1407,181,1919]" captionTargetId="figure-22@16.[179,1407,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="FIGURE 14. Chelonus (Scabrichelonus) nigrifemoratus sp. nov., female, holotype. A, fore wing; B, mesosoma, lateral aspect; C, mesosoma, dorsal aspect; D, metasoma, lateral aspect; E, hind leg; F, head, anterior aspect; G, head, dorsal aspect; H, metasoma, dorsal aspect; I, head, lateral aspect." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6854058" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6854058/files/figure.png" pageId="17" pageNumber="544">Fig. 14G</figureCitation>
); face as long as its width, evenly convex; clypeus flat, sparsely and finely punctate; length of malar space 0.5 × basal width of mandible (
<figureCitation box="[937,1037,727,753]" captionStart="FIGURE 14" captionStartId="16.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[179,1407,181,1919]" captionTargetId="figure-22@16.[179,1407,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="FIGURE 14. Chelonus (Scabrichelonus) nigrifemoratus sp. nov., female, holotype. A, fore wing; B, mesosoma, lateral aspect; C, mesosoma, dorsal aspect; D, metasoma, lateral aspect; E, hind leg; F, head, anterior aspect; G, head, dorsal aspect; H, metasoma, dorsal aspect; I, head, lateral aspect." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6854058" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6854058/files/figure.png" pageId="17" pageNumber="544">Fig. 14F</figureCitation>
); face and eyes with densely setose in lateral view (
<figureCitation box="[327,419,763,789]" captionStart="FIGURE 14" captionStartId="16.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[179,1407,181,1919]" captionTargetId="figure-22@16.[179,1407,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="FIGURE 14. Chelonus (Scabrichelonus) nigrifemoratus sp. nov., female, holotype. A, fore wing; B, mesosoma, lateral aspect; C, mesosoma, dorsal aspect; D, metasoma, lateral aspect; E, hind leg; F, head, anterior aspect; G, head, dorsal aspect; H, metasoma, dorsal aspect; I, head, lateral aspect." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6854058" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6854058/files/figure.png" pageId="17" pageNumber="544">Fig. 14I</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
