<emphasis bold="true" box="[586,599,2015,2039]" pageId="18" pageNumber="545">J</emphasis>
, antenna; 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[703,723,2015,2039]" pageId="18" pageNumber="545">K</emphasis>
, metasoma, posterior aspect.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph blockId="19.[151,1437,150,968]" pageId="19" pageNumber="546">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,332,150,176]" pageId="19" pageNumber="546">Mesosoma.</emphasis>
Length of mesosoma 2.2 × its height; pronotum densely irregularly reticulate; mesoscutum evenly convex, irregularly finely reticulate-rugose, more strongly and coarsely rugose postero-medially; scutellum finely punctate-rugose; scutellar sulcus narrow, with 7 carinae; propodeum densely reticulate-rugose (
<figureCitation box="[1240,1345,222,248]" captionStart="FIGURE 14" captionStartId="16.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[179,1407,181,1919]" captionTargetId="figure-22@16.[179,1407,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="FIGURE 14. Chelonus (Scabrichelonus) nigrifemoratus sp. nov., female, holotype. A, fore wing; B, mesosoma, lateral aspect; C, mesosoma, dorsal aspect; D, metasoma, lateral aspect; E, hind leg; F, head, anterior aspect; G, head, dorsal aspect; H, metasoma, dorsal aspect; I, head, lateral aspect." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6854058" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6854058/files/figure.png" pageId="19" pageNumber="546">Fig. 14C</figureCitation>
); mesopleuron evenly convex, densely finely reticulate-rugose, more strongly and coarsely so antero-dorsally; prepectal carina just extending to level of postero-ventral margin of pronotum; metapleuron coarsely rugose (
<figureCitation box="[1265,1368,294,320]" captionStart="FIGURE 14" captionStartId="16.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[179,1407,181,1919]" captionTargetId="figure-22@16.[179,1407,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="FIGURE 14. Chelonus (Scabrichelonus) nigrifemoratus sp. nov., female, holotype. A, fore wing; B, mesosoma, lateral aspect; C, mesosoma, dorsal aspect; D, metasoma, lateral aspect; E, hind leg; F, head, anterior aspect; G, head, dorsal aspect; H, metasoma, dorsal aspect; I, head, lateral aspect." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6854058" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6854058/files/figure.png" pageId="19" pageNumber="546">Fig. 14B</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="19.[151,1437,150,968]" pageId="19" pageNumber="546">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,282,330,356]" pageId="19" pageNumber="546">Wings.</emphasis>
Fore wing (
<figureCitation box="[417,522,330,356]" captionStart="FIGURE 14" captionStartId="16.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[179,1407,181,1919]" captionTargetId="figure-22@16.[179,1407,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="FIGURE 14. Chelonus (Scabrichelonus) nigrifemoratus sp. nov., female, holotype. A, fore wing; B, mesosoma, lateral aspect; C, mesosoma, dorsal aspect; D, metasoma, lateral aspect; E, hind leg; F, head, anterior aspect; G, head, dorsal aspect; H, metasoma, dorsal aspect; I, head, lateral aspect." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6854058" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6854058/files/figure.png" pageId="19" pageNumber="546">Fig. 14A</figureCitation>
): length of fore wing 3.0 × its width; length of vein 1-R1 0.9 × length of pterostigma; vein 2-R1 just present; r: 3-SR: SRl =11: 19: 70; parastigma slightly swollen; 1-CU1: 2-CU1 = 13:46; vein CUlb present.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="19.[151,1437,150,968]" pageId="19" pageNumber="546">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,262,438,464]" pageId="19" pageNumber="546">Legs.</emphasis>
Hind coxa shallowly punctate-rugose; hind femur robust, its length 3.1 × its width; hind tibia rather thick apically, its length 1.2 × length of tarsus; hind tarsus narrowed towards apex; length of basitarsus 0.4 × length of tarsus, 2.0 × length of inner tibial spur (
<figureCitation box="[595,697,510,536]" captionStart="FIGURE 14" captionStartId="16.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[179,1407,181,1919]" captionTargetId="figure-22@16.[179,1407,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="FIGURE 14. Chelonus (Scabrichelonus) nigrifemoratus sp. nov., female, holotype. A, fore wing; B, mesosoma, lateral aspect; C, mesosoma, dorsal aspect; D, metasoma, lateral aspect; E, hind leg; F, head, anterior aspect; G, head, dorsal aspect; H, metasoma, dorsal aspect; I, head, lateral aspect." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6854058" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6854058/files/figure.png" pageId="19" pageNumber="546">Fig. 14E</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="19.[151,1437,150,968]" pageId="19" pageNumber="546">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,331,546,572]" pageId="19" pageNumber="546">Metasoma.</emphasis>
Length of metasoma 2.8 × its maximum width in dorsal view; metasomal carapace longitudinally densely reticulate-rugose (
<figureCitation box="[452,559,582,608]" captionStart="FIGURE 14" captionStartId="16.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[179,1407,181,1919]" captionTargetId="figure-22@16.[179,1407,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="FIGURE 14. Chelonus (Scabrichelonus) nigrifemoratus sp. nov., female, holotype. A, fore wing; B, mesosoma, lateral aspect; C, mesosoma, dorsal aspect; D, metasoma, lateral aspect; E, hind leg; F, head, anterior aspect; G, head, dorsal aspect; H, metasoma, dorsal aspect; I, head, lateral aspect." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6854058" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6854058/files/figure.png" pageId="19" pageNumber="546">Fig. 14H</figureCitation>
); ovipositor is hidden under the ventral opening of metasomal carapace, the ovipositor sheath 0.12 × as long as fore wing, 0.31 × as long as hind tibia (
<figureCitation box="[987,1091,618,644]" captionStart="FIGURE 14" captionStartId="16.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[179,1407,181,1919]" captionTargetId="figure-22@16.[179,1407,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="FIGURE 14. Chelonus (Scabrichelonus) nigrifemoratus sp. nov., female, holotype. A, fore wing; B, mesosoma, lateral aspect; C, mesosoma, dorsal aspect; D, metasoma, lateral aspect; E, hind leg; F, head, anterior aspect; G, head, dorsal aspect; H, metasoma, dorsal aspect; I, head, lateral aspect." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6854058" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6854058/files/figure.png" pageId="19" pageNumber="546">Fig. 14D</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="19.[151,1437,150,968]" pageId="19" pageNumber="546">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,288,654,680]" pageId="19" pageNumber="546">Colour.</emphasis>
Black; antennomeres blackish-brown; palp yellowish brown; scapus (except for base) and mandibles basally reddish-brown; pterostigma and most of veins blackish-brown; basal third of carapace yellowish; legs almost yellowish-brown totally; hind соха blасk but apically yellowish-brown; hind femur blackish-brown; basal hind tibia light yellow and apically brown.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="19.[151,1437,150,968]" pageId="19" pageNumber="546">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,264,798,824]" pageId="19" pageNumber="546">male.</emphasis>
Antennomeres 30; similar to female, but differs in entirely black carapace (
<figureCitation box="[1097,1263,798,824]" captionStart="FIGURE 16" captionStartId="18.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[179,1407,181,1919]" captionTargetId="figure-22@18.[179,1407,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="FIGURE 16. Chelonus (Scabrichelonus) nigrifemoratus sp. nov., male, paratypes. A, fore wing; B, mesosoma, lateral aspect; C, mesosoma, dorsal aspect; D, metasoma, lateral aspect; E, metasoma, dorsal aspect; F, hind leg; G, head, anterior aspect; H, head, dorsal aspect; I, head, lateral aspect; J, antenna; K, metasoma, posterior aspect." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6854062" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6854062/files/figure.png" pageId="19" pageNumber="546">Figs 16D, 16E</figureCitation>
); carapace with a small apical opening which transverse elongate-oval in posterior view, 2.3 × wider than high, and height of opening 0.5 × ventral height of carapace (
<figureCitation box="[564,668,870,896]" captionStart="FIGURE 16" captionStartId="18.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[179,1407,181,1919]" captionTargetId="figure-22@18.[179,1407,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="FIGURE 16. Chelonus (Scabrichelonus) nigrifemoratus sp. nov., male, paratypes. A, fore wing; B, mesosoma, lateral aspect; C, mesosoma, dorsal aspect; D, metasoma, lateral aspect; E, metasoma, dorsal aspect; F, hind leg; G, head, anterior aspect; H, head, dorsal aspect; I, head, lateral aspect; J, antenna; K, metasoma, posterior aspect." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6854062" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6854062/files/figure.png" pageId="19" pageNumber="546">Fig. 16K</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
